From: michaelkremenetsky
 <28833521+michaelkremenetsky@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 04:39:26 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 14/15] turbo-tasks-fs: skip watching nonexistent dirs on wasi

On wasi, notify falls back to PollWatcher, which registers a nonexistent
path and then reports it as an asynchronous ErrorKind::Io(NotFound) event
(a noisy "watch error" line plus a spurious invalidation) instead of the
synchronous ErrorKind::PathNotFound that inotify returns and
start_watching_dir already swallows. Match the inotify semantics by
skipping the registration; the parent directory stays watched, so
restore_if_watched re-arms the path if it is created later.
---
 turbopack/crates/turbo-tasks-fs/src/watcher.rs | 13 +++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 13 insertions(+)

diff --git a/turbopack/crates/turbo-tasks-fs/src/watcher.rs b/turbopack/crates/turbo-tasks-fs/src/watcher.rs
index 140ecb1b..bef57c3b 100644
--- a/turbopack/crates/turbo-tasks-fs/src/watcher.rs
+++ b/turbopack/crates/turbo-tasks-fs/src/watcher.rs
@@ -266,6 +266,19 @@ mod non_recursive_helpers {
     ) -> Result<()> {
         debug_assert_ne!(dir_path, root_path);
 
+        // On wasi, notify falls back to `PollWatcher`, which registers a
+        // nonexistent path and then reports it as an asynchronous
+        // `ErrorKind::Io(NotFound)` event (a noisy "watch error" line plus a
+        // spurious invalidation) instead of the synchronous
+        // `ErrorKind::PathNotFound` that inotify returns and the match below
+        // swallows. Match the inotify semantics by skipping the registration;
+        // the parent directory stays watched, so `restore_if_watched` re-arms
+        // this path if it is created later.
+        #[cfg(target_os = "wasi")]
+        if !dir_path.exists() {
+            return Ok(());
+        }
+
         match notify_watcher.watch(dir_path, RecursiveMode::NonRecursive) {
             Ok(())
             | Err(notify::Error {
